MQ135 Gas Sensor – For detecting harmful gases and air quality (PPM levels).

NodeMCU ESP8266 – Microcontroller with Wi-Fi capabilities for data transmission.

DHT11 Sensor – Measures temperature and humidity.

Relay Module – Controls external devices (like an exhaust fan).

Buzzer Module – Provides an alert sound when air quality is poor.

Power Supply (5V or USB Adapter) – To power the NodeMCU.

Jumper Wires – For making connections.

Breadboard (Optional) – For easy prototyping.

Adafruit IO Account – For IoT dashboard and data visualization.
